Sometimes the most important mentoring happens quietly at the kitchen table.

Over the weekend I helped my nephew sign off on his final review to complete his computer programming course. We also worked through cloud access and identity concepts in Amazon Web Services, including AWS Identity and Access Management.

Seeing someone finish their course and step confidently into tech is rewarding.

Sometimes support, guidance, and a bit of encouragement are all someone needs to get across the finish line.

